the global exposures
related to purchased components and materials are such that a 1% price change
would result in a pre-tax cost or savings of approximately $55 million per
year. the global energy exposure is such that a 10% price change would result
in a pre-tax cost or savings of approximately $35 million per year. derivative
instruments are used to hedge less than 2% of the purchased components and
materials exposure and are used to hedge approximately 10% of this energy
exposure.
